      "Hi @mr-world -- that looks pretty good and surprisingly consistent with our style, except that some code is invalid.  The use of EINTR around `close(2)` system calls is questionable.  Please see http://www.daemonology.net/blog/2011-12-17-POSIX-close-is-broken.html .  We have adopted the practice of ignoring EINTR around `close` calls."
